Two important points:
Builsing distributed Systems still means your Maschine dies bot work because some Computer you die Not knownabout failed

Builsing ds is now very easy thanks to Cloud Provisioning. Sometimes it seems as ifnwe let Engineering build distributed Systems simply because it is fashionable and Fun
However stmt 1 still holds: builsing a ds always means introducing werid errors (Network, doenstream errors...)

If you decide to build a ds think about which the Level of consistency every Level of Data requires. Theb decide what softeare to use (eg Mongo for Data that can be recobstruczed)

Two reasons for building a ds: scalability and fault tolerance. Unfort the two work against each other 